  "doc_id": "6421",
  "text": "FFCD is a benign condition first described in 1985 by Bell et al. [CITATION_1] , which is probably caused by a failure of differentiation in the pes anserinus area resulting in a growth disturbance of the proximal tibia along with varus deformity. Up to date there have been about 92 published cases of FFCD, the majority occurring in the proximal tibia (n=67), fewer in the femur (n=11), ulna (n=7), humerus (n=3), radius (n=2) or phalanx (n=2).",
  "correct_citation": {
